4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING A TAX CREDIT FOR THE BIRTH OF A CHILD;
5 PROVIDING A MAXIMUM REFUNDABLE CREDIT AMOUNT; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY;
6 AMENDING SECTION 15-30-2303, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN APPLICABILITY DATE.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Birth day tax credit -- rulemaking. (1) A resident taxpayer is allowed a
11 credit against the tax imposed by 15-30-2103 or 15-30-2151 in the year in which a taxpayer's child is born.
12 (2) Subject to subsections (5) and (6), the amount of the credit allowed under subsection (1) is
13 equal to the lesser of $3,000 or the total of:
14 (a) Montana income taxes due in the tax year;
15 (b) federal income taxes due in the tax year; and
16 (c) the taxpayer's employee contributions in the tax year under the Federal Insurance
17 Contributions Act pursuant to 26 U.S.C. 3111.
18 (3) To claim the credit under this section, the taxpayer shall include on the tax return the name and
19 location of the birth of the child and the names of the child's parents as listed on the birth certificate.
20 (4) The taxpayer is entitled to a refund equal to the amount by which the credit exceeds the
21 taxpayer's tax liability or, if the taxpayer has no tax liability under this chapter, a refund equal to the amount of
22 the credit. The credit may be claimed by filing a Montana income tax return.
23 (5) The credit in subsection (2) is reduced at a rate of $150 for each $1,000 of a taxpayer's federal
24 adjusted gross income in excess of:
25 (a) $120,000 if the taxpayer is married filing jointly; or
26 (b) $60,000 for all other filing statuses.
27 (6) (a) The maximum credit calculated under subsections (2) and (5) is $1,500 if:
28 (i) the parents are married to each other and use the married filing separately filing status; or
